-- Zambian Mining Companies to Pay $300 Million in Tax Arrears, Minister Says
-- B y   O b e r t   S i m w a n z a
-- 2010-11-25T16:38:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-25/zambian-mining-companies-to-pay-300-million-in-tax-arrears-minister-says.html
Zambian mining companies agreed to
pay 1.4 trillion kwacha ($300 million) in tax arrears by June,
2011, Finance Minister Situmbeko Musokotwane told lawmakers in
the capital, Lusaka, today. The arrears stem from changes to the
tax regime in 2008.  Mining companies have also agreed to a 30 percent corporate
tax rate, a 3 percent royalty and a 15 percent variable profit
tax, Musokotwane said.  “Mining collections will tremendously increase,” he
said,  To contact the reporter on this story:
Obert Simwanza in Lusaka at 
